        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 2:52PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Columbus, or near Tigerville, moving southeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campobello, Tigerville, Landrum, Glassy Mountain, Gowensville, and
North Saluda Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
